    "plan_content": "## Plan: Add Model Rename Feature to Ollama (4 files, 7 edits)\n\n### What I found in the codebase\n\nAll relevant patterns were confirmed by reading the actual source. Here's the mapping:\n\n| Existing Pattern | Location |\n|---|---|\n| `CopyRequest` struct | `api/types.go` line 762 |\n| `Client.Copy()` | `api/client.go` line 382 |\n| `CopyHandler` on `*Server` | `server/routes.go` line 1446 |\n| `DeleteHandler` on `*Server` | `server/routes.go` line 1055 |\n| `getExistingName()` helper | `server/routes.go` line 1031 |\n| Route `/api/copy` registration | `server/routes.go` line 1698 |\n| CLI `CopyHandler` func | `cmd/cmd.go` line 1338 |\n| `copyCmd` cobra command | `cmd/cmd.go` line 2257 |\n| `rootCmd.AddCommand()` | `cmd/cmd.go` line 2331 |\n| `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg = \"invalid model name\"` | `types/errtypes/errtypes.go` line 11 |\n\n---\n\n### The 7 changes\n\n**`api/types.go`** — Add `RenameRequest` struct after `CopyRequest` (line 765), identical field names/JSON tags.\n\n**`api/client.go`** — Add `Client.Rename()` after `Client.Copy()` (line 387), calling `POST /api/rename`.\n\n**`server/routes.go`** — Add `RenameHandler` method after `CopyHandler` (line 1483):\n- Parse JSON body → check non-empty Source/Destination → 400\n- Validate both names with `model.ParseName()`/`IsValid()` → 400 with `errtypes.InvalidModelNameErrMsg`\n- Canonicalize src via `getExistingName(src)` → 404 if error\n- Canonicalize dst via `getExistingName(dst)`\n- Check dst already exists via `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(dst)` → **409 Conflict** if found\n- `CopyModel(src, dst)` → 404 if `os.ErrNotExist`, 500 otherwise\n- `manifest.ParseNamedManifest(src)` → `m.Remove()` → `m.RemoveLayers()` → 500 on error\n- Return `200 {\"status\":\"success\"}`\n\n**`server/routes.go`** — Register `r.POST(\"/api/rename\", s.RenameHandler)` after line 1698 (`/api/copy`).\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`** — Add `RenameHandler` func after `CopyHandler` (line 1350), printing `Renamed \"X\" to \"Y\"`.\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`** — Add `renameCmd` cobra command after `copyCmd` definition (line 2263) with `ExactArgs(2)`.\n\n**`cmd/cmd.go`** — Insert `renameCmd` into `rootCmd.AddCommand()` between `copyCmd` and `deleteCmd` (line 2345).\n\n> **No new imports needed** — all required packages are already imported in each file.",
